# Go vendored dependencies

## Rule
Go services vendor their dependencies (`go mod vendor`). Dockerfiles build with `-mod=vendor`. `vendor/` is committed.

## Why
Vendored builds are reproducible offline, immune to upstream module removals, and match the pattern every Go service in this workspace already uses.

## Constraints
- `go mod tidy && go mod vendor` is part of the "dependency change" workflow; both files and the `vendor/` tree are committed together.
- Dockerfile builds invoke `go build -mod=vendor`; never `-mod=mod` in release images.
- `vendor/` is not gitignored.
- CI verifies `go mod verify` and that `vendor/` matches `go.mod`.

## Examples

### Good
> PR includes `go.mod`, `go.sum`, and the resulting `vendor/` subtree. CI's `go mod verify` and `go build -mod=vendor ./...` pass.

### Bad
> PR changes `go.mod` only; `vendor/` drifts.

